	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Maximiss' Paladin guide #1</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:kornfreakonleash@hotmail.com">Justin Hoover</a> | 
		            7/30/2001 5:57:47 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">-Go to your guild in North Freeport (Hall of Truth). Go to the roof and give the note to the guild leader and get your Tunic and some XP.<BR>
-Before you start fighting you need to set up your hot buttons. Equip your sword and have the melee attack at the top left corner and taunt to the right of it and sense heading below them and Lay Hands at the bottom. (Be sure not to hit Lay Hands while your targeting to enemy it will fill their gauge not yours=).<BR>
 - Do what every newbie does fight all the monsters in your newbie zone looting EVERYTHING! (Note: see a wolf and haul @ss to the guards at level 1 and 2 and if you see orc pawns make sure you have your lay hands ready if not fight near the guards and bail when your hp gets low)<BR>
- At level 4 or 5 you are ready to go to East commons and fight low-level creatures with the occasional black bear. {Right click everything.  Only take yellow monsters with Lay Hands.) Do this till about level 7.<BR>
* Watch out as you venture farther out into the commons where there are lions, pumas, young Kodiaks. They will agro on you quick.<BR>
*Now here is the money part- the moneymakers are High quality bear skins-20pp<BR>
Stack of bone chips (20 in a stack)-they go for 5pp<BR>
-Once you are level six train one point in bashing at your guild in North Freeport. This proves to be very useful because you do more damage.  Now go to the inn at very back of the zone and buy a descent shield.<BR>
-When you get around 50 -60pp start advertising <BR>
/auction WTB BRONZE ARMOR PLZ SEND A TELL<BR>
-This is excellent armor for your level. Some people will try to take advantage of and overprice you. Always get them to tell you their price first and offer half and say you&#8217;re broke and desperate. Be patient just the other day I got a full suit to help out a friend for 1 Deathfist belt (I will mention these later on)!!!! Get as close to a full suit as you can. You should pay no more than 65pp for a full suit no matter what. There will always be a lower price so just be patient.<BR>
-Pending on how much you paid for your bronze armor, you are going to want to get another weapon (That is if you already haven&#8217;t).  A good place to get a weapon is either at your guild or at Groflah&#8217;s forge.  You will want to get either a 2hs or a 1hs.  I recommend 1hs so that  you can still use your shield but that&#8217;s just me. Look for a bastard sword they are great.<BR>
-Lets get back to business, now that your level 7 possibly with a little or a full set of bronze armor, a shield, and a descent sword, you need to kick some orc arse at either of the 2 camps.  Get in a group and just level up.  Don&#8217;t get side tracked, just level up.  Now as your leveling up you will notice that you are looting lots of Orc deathfist slashed belts.  You can either give them to Captain Hadden ( I think) in the militia house or Cain Dunmoore ( I think)  at the steel warriors guild. Hand them in 2 at a time.  If you&#8217;re a true knight you will give them all to Cain like I did, but that is also a good way to get KoS to the militia.  Hehe.  Just to be safe hand in 2 to Cain TWICE and 2 to Captain TWICE.<BR>
-You will fly through the levels with this method that has been handed down from Paladin to Paladin.<BR>
-DING&#8230;OMG you hit level 9 and you get the gitters.  Its time to transform from a weak warrior to a mighty Paladin.  Go to your guild and buy all of your spells, scribe them, and memorize them.  Then just go to the gate and buff everyone you see. They will thank you and think you are the sh%#.  Then you can go ahead and resume fighting the orcs till level 11 or 12.  At that point you need a magical weapon to fight willowisps in west commons. Keep your eyes peeled for all the young kodiaks.  Remember they carry HQ bear skins so kill them when you see them.  Guess what along with a magical weapon you need a magical shield to bash willowisps.  They 2 I  recommend are the shiny brass shield (Provides Light at night too) and the combine long sword which you can obtain at the Gypsy camp in Oasis. Be careful for Sand Giants and Spectres, they hurt really bad.<BR>
-Just keep advertising that your looking for a shiny brass shield and sooner or later you&#8217;ll get one.  Pay about 20pp for it. <BR>
-These willowisps carry excellent loot that you can sell to vendors, so just keep wacking away till you get really loaded.  Do this till about level 13 or 14 ( some people have more skills at this game that others) and go fight dervs at the derv camp in west commons.  They carry great loot also so just keep selling and keep getting more and more loaded with platinum. (Don&#8217;t forget those HQ bear skins either). Fight dervs for about a level or so and head to oasis to fight all the crocs and caimans. They have horrible loot.  Infact they don&#8217;t have any besides gator meat and a chunk of meat.  So bear with me.<BR>
-You can fight these guys till about level 16.  Don&#8217;t forget to stop by your guild at level 15 to pick up your new spells.<BR>
* Note : If you hadn&#8217;t  figured it out already Courage and Holy armor stack.  Along with the buffs just keep hitting the yaulp spell( you can only cast it on yourself during a fight).  This will help you land more attacks.  You are starting to become godlike for your level.<BR>
-Ok at level 16 or 17 you must venture to Highpass hold to fight GNOLLS at first.  You should camp the Polished Granite Tomahawk and the Shralok pack.  The pack has 8 slots and has a 25% decrease in weight!!! That is a must for getting a ton of loot when you are a heavy tank.<BR>
-Do this till level 19.  At level 19 go to the Orc side where you will get excellent experience. If you happen to be dumb as a rock, stay in a group!(For the idiots)<BR>
-Ok now you can level up to level 20 on the orc camp.<BR>
-Now that your level 20 you can buy a descent weapon.  There is a cap that prevents you from hitting over 29 or 30 points of damage. Yeah now you know why that great weapon of yours just absolutely sucks.<BR>
-The weapon you want to buy is the Blackened Iron Bastard Sword (BIBS). If you have a high attack and strength you can hit upwards to 57 with this bad boy.  But there are lots of good weapons out there and you may want to buy something else.  But you should buy this sword for around 250pp.  Yes your thinking holy shi% that&#8217;s a lot of money.  But its worth it.  <BR>
-Well so far I have basically explained what I have done in my 20 levels of knight hood.  So basically what I have done is taken a lot of different Info that I have gotten and made a better, revised version.<BR>
-Right now I am a level 20 Paladin on the Morell Thule server with a set of Orc Fang Earings and a full suit of bronze armor with the exception of my Blackened alloy Mail.<BR>
My name is Maximiss Reinquist and my e-mail is kornfreakonleash@hotmail.com.  And please stay ready for my next Paladin guide for levels 20 to 35 or there abouts.<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
